Package evs.data.fileio

Classes for file I/O.

See:
          Description

Interface Summary
InputDataIO Interface for reading files that contain forecasts or observations.
 

Class Summary
ASCIIFileIO Reads ASCII files containing forecasts or observations.
FileIO Base class for file reading and writing files.
FileIOUtilities Utility class for file writing
GlobalUnitsReader Class comprising static methods for reading in global units, such as time systems and measurement units.
InputFileFilter A convenience implementation of FileFilter that filters out all files except for those type extensions that it knows about.
NetCDFEnsembleHandler Handler for time-series files in the NetCDF format.
NetCDFFileIO Reads one or more time-series files in the NetCDF.
NetCDFSingleValuedHandler Handler for time-series files in the NetCDF format.
OHDFileIO ALL TIME ZONES IN THIS CLASS MUST RETURN INTEGER OFFSETS IN MILLISECONDS RELATIVE TO UTC FROM getRawOffset().
PairedFileIO Reads and writes paired data files in XML format and generates a paired dataset from an analysis unit containing an appropriate file data source.
PairedFileSAXHandler Handler for reading paired files in XML format using the SAX model.
PISAXHandler Handler for time-series files in the Published Interface (PI) XML format, for which a schema is available from: http://fews.wldelft.nl/schemas/version1.0/pi-schemas/pi_timeseries.xsd Reads files containing ensemble forecasts and files containing observations.
ProjectFileIO Class for reading and writing project files in XMLW format.
PublishedInterfaceXMLIO Reads one or more time-series files in the Published Interface (PI) XML format, for which a schema is available from: http://fews.wldelft.nl/schemas/version1.0/pi-schemas/pi_timeseries.xsd Reads both files containing ensemble forecasts and files containing observations.
ResultFileIO Writes metric results to file in XML format.
WriteOption Class of options for writing graphical and numerical results.
XMLW Extends ECS XML element for pretty printing by default.
XSLTControl Controls the conversion of an XML file to another format defined by an stylesheet using XSLT.
